items.name: Hellsing Wiki
items.title: Hellsing Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to The Hellsing Wiki
items.desc:
The Hellsing Organization, a secret branch of the British government, has long been battling supernatural threats to keep the people safe from creatures of the night. Its current leader, Sir Integra Hellsing, controls her own personal army to eliminate the undead beings, but even her highly trained soldiers pale in comparison to her most trusted vampire exterminator, Alucard, who is actually a powerful vampire himself. Along with Integra's mysterious butler and Alucard's new vampire minion, Seras Victoria, the Hellsing Organization must face not only regular ghouls and vampires, but a rivaling secret branch of the Vatican and an mysterious group of madmen spawned by a certain war over 50 years ago.
The original Hellsing manga by Kouta Hirano ran 10 volumes, finishing in 2008. The Hellsing anime followed a different storyline, but with the same main characters. The dub ran in the United States from October 4, 2003 to December 27, 2003 on Starz!'s Encore Action cable channel.
The Hellsing OVA started at 2006, once completed will features 10 Episodes and, unlike the anime, it follows the manga more closely.

items.title: Dead Rising Wiki
items.headline: The wikia about Dead Rising that anyone can edit.
items.desc:
Dead Rising is a survival horror video game set in an open world environment. It is developed and published by Capcom and produced by Keiji Inafune. It was released on August 8, 2006 exclusively for the Xbox 360 video game console.

Dead Rising's story centers on Frank West, a photojournalist who ends up trapped in a shopping mall in the fictional town of Willamette, Colorado, that is infested with zombies.

items.title: All About Singing Fish! Wiki
items.headline: Learn the history of those singing fish at the All About Singing Fish wiki!
items.desc:
Remember that singing fish popular in 1999 - Big Mouth Billy Bass?
He's the one everyone remembers, but did you know there were more than just Billy:  Trout, Catfish, crustaceans, crocodiles, swordfish, countless Billy Bass knock-offs, and even fish skeletons!
At the All About Singing Fish wiki, you can learn about all the other not so famous fish. You'll be really - and I mean really - surprised by how many copycat products there are!

items.name: Animal Crossing New Leaf Wiki
items.title: Animal Crossing New Leaf Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Animal Crossing New Leaf Wiki!
items.desc:
Welcome to the Animal Crossing New Leaf Wiki, the wiki about Animal Crossing: New Leaf that anyone can edit! 

Animal Crossing: New Leaf (とびだせ どうぶつの森 Tobidase Dōbutsu no Mori?, "Animal Forest: Jump Out") is a life simulation video game for the Nintendo 3DS console and the fourth main title in Nintendo's Animal Crossing series, where the player character lives in a rural village populated with anthropomorphic animals. In this installment, the player takes control of the mayor instead of a normal villager. The game was first released on November 8, 2012, in Japan and was later released in North America, Europe and Australia in June 2013. The game has received very positive reviews, gaining aggregate scores of 88 and 87.30% on Metacritic and GameRankings, so far making it the highest rated game in the Animal Crossing series.
